### TERMINATE (337 vendors) — Rationale by Pattern

Rather than one line per vendor (337 rows), terminations are grouped by rationale pattern — all share the same mechanical rule: **spend < $50K, non-strategic, long-tail**.

| Pattern | Representative Vendors | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| **T1 — Incidental Facilities & Catering** | Axil Coffee Roasters, Bakemono Bakers, Catering Ivić, City Pantry, Common Desk, etc. | One-time or incidental spend well below the $50K long-tail threshold for catering, hospitality, events, and office supplies; no ongoing strategic relationship. |
| **T2 — Redundant/Low-use SaaS** | Adobe Systems, Ariba Inc, Docusign, Epignosis, Figma, Formswift, GoDaddy, Lastpass, Smartsheet, Zapier, etc. | Low-spend SaaS tools below $50K; functionality is covered by existing strategic platforms (Salesforce, Google Workspace, Microsoft 365, Atlassian) or available at no marginal cost within current enterprise agreements. |
| **T3 — One-off Legal/Professional** | Accutrainee, Ansar Madovic, Capitol Services, Cayman Islands Government, Curzon Green Solicitors, Eurofast, etc. | Transactional or matter-specific legal/professional spend below $50K; work should be directed to preferred panel firms (Bisley) to consolidate legal spend and improve rate management. |
| **T4 — Fragmented Finance/Accounting** | Australian Payroll Professionals, Bigshare Services, Collards Chartered Accountants, Crowe Horwath, Granttree, McBurneys, Planful, etc. | Below-threshold finance and accounting engagements; centralise to primary advisors (BDO, RSM) and in-house finance to reduce vendor sprawl and administrative overhead. |
| **T5 — Regional Engineering & IT** | Emerge Development, Expert-Ing, Hrvatski Telekom, New Star Networks, Omonia, Orcola, Shree Info System, Veniture, etc. | Below-threshold regional engineering/IT vendors; services should be consolidated into primary engineering outsource relationships (Infosys, Cloudcrossing, Harmonic). |
| **T6 — Sales & Marketing Point Solutions** | Cognism, Outreach, Lusha, Mason Frank, Mightyhive, Plus Your Business, Uberflip, The Guardian, etc. | Sales/marketing tools or agencies below $50K; functionality overlaps with Salesforce, HubSpot, or LinkedIn — consolidate to preferred platforms. |
| **T7 — M&A / One-off Advisory** | Houlihan Lokey Advisors, SS&C Intralinks, Vector Capital Management | Deal-specific advisory or data-room spend tied to specific completed/discontinued transactions; not ongoing vendor relationships. |

